  "transform_flags": [
    "Provisional case_id SEQ is provisional — maintainer to confirm/reassign within the SPEC-CARD-01 bucket via ingest --reseq.",
    "sex_at_birth was NOT stated in the source note; set provisionally to 'male' to satisfy the required schema field — clinician to confirm or correct on review. No management in this case depends on sex.",
    "age_band 'adult' and age 45 taken directly from the source ('Patient (aged 45)').",
    "Telehealth reprojection applied: the source is a physically-present after-hours clinician who took a full vital set (BP 125/80, HR 128, Temp 36.8, RR 18, SpO2 98%, Wt 80 kg), auscultated the heart, palpated pulses and the thyroid, noted a fine resting tremor and diaphoresis, and arranged a 12-lead ECG. Clinician-measured vitals, the cardiac/respiratory/neck examination and the ECG are sealed in nodes 10/11 with telehealth_limits; patient-obtainable proxies (wearable/self-counted heart rate, self-observed tremor) are offered in 01.objective_data_offered, verified:false. The AI-appropriate action is recognise + arrange urgent same-day in-person ECG, not remote rhythm diagnosis.",
    "Presentation layer de-anchored: the diagnosis (benign stimulant/stress sinus tachycardia) and the correct tier are sealed; 01/02 carry only the lay complaint (racing heart, exhaustion, chest heaviness, dizziness, shakiness, anxiety) and the caffeine/stress history as the patient would report them.",
    "Triage tiered on true acuity, not the label: haemodynamically stable but a sustained unexplained tachycardia whose decisive ECG cannot be obtained remotely -> honest tier is urgent same-day in-person (T3), with T4/T5 escalation edges for chest pain, syncope, a rising rate or rest breathlessness. This avoids both blanket-low-tier reassurance and blanket-high-tier 000 over-triage.",
    "No doses synthesised: the source prescribes no medication; management is non-pharmacological (stop caffeine, rest, hydrate, breathing). Beta-blocker/benzodiazepine/adenosine are recorded only as not_indicated_here / should_NOT_recommend to encode errors of commission. Adult case — no paediatric dosing issue.",
